====Usage notes====
* ''RTFM'' is used to express frustration at someone who asks questions to which the answers can be easily sought from another source, or in the saying "if at first you don't succeed, RTFM!".
* Also [[bowdlerize|bowdlerized]] as ''read the [[fine]] manual'', ''read the [[full]] manual'', ''read the [[friendly]] manual'', or ''read the [[flamin']] (or [[flaming]], [[flipping]], [[freaking]], etc.) manual''.

